 Aliwal North - Members of the Aliwal North Stock Theft and endangered species Unit managed to successfully arrest five suspects for stock theft. "On Friday, during the morning hours the members of Aliwal North STES follwed up positive information and arrested five suspects and recovered 30 sheep that was loaded in a BAW combi," said police spokesperson, Capt Ursula Roelofse. "These suspects is also alleged to be part of a cindicate operating all over the Eastern Cape as well as the Free State. "The five suspects aged between 39 and 22 years old." She added that these suspects will appear in the Aliwal North Magistrate's Court on Monday. Aliwal North SAPS Deputy Cluster Commander, Col Mpho Rabela, commended the members on the excellent success as stock theft is a priority crime in our area. "The arrest of the members of the syndicate will also make the linkage to other cases possible." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 